#441
The Grave Tunnel Hinge~
Where the old pre-civic burial tunnel meets the surface approach to the Thornwood estate. This is the transit node shared with Shadowmere's southern march supply routes and Midgaard's funeral convoy traffic â neutral infrastructure neither power controls. The tunnel ceiling is low and sweating limestone, braced with timber so old it has calcified. Carved way-markers from at least three distinct traditions overlap on the eastern wall: a civic registry glyph from Midgaard's road-standards era, a directional slash-mark used by Shadowmere's tunnel scouts, and something older and non-linguistic â a pressed handprint in ochre that may predate the tunnel's formal construction. The smell is mineral and cold, with an undertone of old bone and something faintly sweet that does not belong underground.
