The surface world above the tunnel hinge, where the estate's cobblestone road begins. The paving is ancient and frost-heaved, pushed up in long ridges by root masses that have been growing beneath it for generations. The stones are dark with moisture even in dry weather â the substrate draws groundwater upward through the limestone below. To the north, the road curves toward a silhouette of iron and thorn against a canopy of leafless oaks. Crows occupy every available branch, unmoving.
